      "content": "While RICE and ibuprofen are standard for minor strains, your description suggests something more significant than a simple tweak. If the pain is severe and the ankle feels like it might give out, you need to be more certain than just waiting. I advise you to take a high-quality, non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug like naproxen, but definitely monitor it closely. If the swelling doesn't visibly decrease within 48 hours, you should seek professional evaluation to rule out a fracture.",
